The paper deals with computer vision techniques for identifying the pose and location of objects in 3D from a single 2D image, with a specific focus on vehicles. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also makes use of geometric techniques and machine learning algorithms, which could potentially place it in the categories of graphics (cs.GR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
